## Wrapper scope (least-privilege)

The wrapper exposes ONLY the endpoints {{used_by_agents}} need. Full
endpoint subset documented in `ENDPOINTS.md`. Excluded surface listed
in the same file under "Excluded (least-privilege)".

Why this matters: an agent that reads pages should not be wired to an
MCP that can also delete pages. Wrapper-as-permission-boundary makes
governance simpler than relying on agent prose alone.

